{
  "texts": [
    "Within this theme, researchers investigate the ways in which GeoGebra as a learning tool can be employed to enhance students' mathematics knowledge, such as abilities to solve mathematical problems, particularly in the domains of calculus, functions and calculation.",
    "Substantial body of research has demonstrated GeoGebra's positive impacts on learning mathematics.",
    "Its interactive interface allows for dynamic modeling, experimentation, and visualization that engages students and brings abstract concepts to life (Ziatdinov & Valles, 2022).",
    "Multiple studies cited have shown GeoGebra improves understanding, performance, and interest across various age groups when incorporated into lesson design (Bhagat & Chang, 2015; Kllogjeri & Kllogjeri, 2015; Yerizon et al., 2021).",
    "Specifically, GeoGebra has proven successful as a tool for developing problem-solving skills."
  ]
}